      • checksum

        public String checksum()
        Description copied from interface: Edit
        A checksum of the opposing sides shadow document. The shadow document must patch strictly and this checksum is used to verify that the other sides shadow document is in fact the same. This can then be used by when before patching to make sure that the shadow documents on both sides are in fact identical.
        Specified by:
        checksum in interface Edit<JsonMergePatchDiff>
        Returns:
        String the opposing side's checksum of the shadow document
